Adjust #oven{} rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Lightly oil empty side, then add @Italian Pork Sausage{9%ounce}.

> For 4 servings, place sausage on a second lightly oiled baking sheet; roast on middle rack.

Roast on top rack until potatoes are browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes} for potatoes and until sausage is cooked through, ~{15-17%minutes} for sausage.

While potatoes and sausage roast, slice @Demi-Baguette{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through. Drizzle with @olive oil{4%teaspoon} and sprinkle with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}.

Place, cut sides up, directly on oven rack. Toast until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

While bread toasts, in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @Marinara Cup{2.5%ounce} and @Cream Cheese{2%tablespoon}.

Microwave for ~{30%seconds}; stir until smooth.

Once sausage is cooked, transfer to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to handle, halve lengthwise. Transfer potato wedges to a #plate{}.

Carefully arrange toasted baguettes on same baking sheet. Spread half the pink sauce onto cut sides. Fill with sausage, then spoon remaining pink sauce over top. Evenly sprinkle with @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup}.

Return to top rack until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @Arugula{2%ounce} with 1 TBSP olive oil (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}.

Fill sandwiches with as much arugula as you like.

Divide sandwiches between plates. Serve with potato wedges and any remaining arugula on the side.